\n\n### Task Title\n**T2: Real-Time Collaborative Document Editor**\n\n### Category\n`greenfield/complex` with 30-minute timeout\n\n### Core Requirements\n\n**1. REST API for Document Management**\n- Create, read, update, list, delete documents\n- Each document has: title, content\n- Version history tracking\n\n**2. WebSocket-based Real-Time Collaboration**\n- Users connect via WebSocket to a document\n- Receive current document state on connect\n- Edits sent as operations (insertions/deletions)\n- Changes broadcast to all connected users\n\n**3. Conflict Resolution**\n- Use Operational Transform (OT) or CRDTs\n- Simultaneous edits must converge to same state\n- Both insertions must be preserved\n- No silent data loss\n\n**4. Persistence**\n- SQLite via better-sqlite3\n- Documents and version history persist\n- Survives server restarts\n\n**5. Robustness**\n- Handle at least 10 concurrent clients on same document\n- No corruption with concurrent edits\n- Graceful error handling (no crashes)\n\n### Structural Requirement\n- Entry point: `src/server.ts` or `src/index.ts`\n- Export `createApp(dbPath?)` factory function\n- Returns object with:\n  - `app` -- HTTP server/Express app\n  - `start(port?)` -- starts listening, returns port (use 0 for random)\n  - `stop()` -- cleanly shuts down server and connections\n\n### Tech Stack\n- TypeScript (pre-configured)\n- Express (HTTP)\n- ws (WebSocket)\n- better-sqlite3 (SQLite)\n- All dependencies pre-installed\n\n### Success Criteria\n- `npm run build` compiles without errors\n- `npm run lint` passes\n- Full lifecycle works: create doc → connect via WS → send edits → broadcast → verify convergence\n- Documents persist across restarts\n- Concurrent edits converge to consistent state\n\n### Tips Provided\n- WebSocket path should include document ID\n- Send sync message with current content on first connect\n- Track document versions for OT\n- Write tests for edge cases\n\n---\n\n## 5. vitest.config.ts\n**Location:** `/workspace/